  "note": "All 102 IL counties covered (102 sheriffs + this note). Primary backbone: IL State Board of Elections 'County Officers' directory (published 2025-12-16), which lists every county sheriff with party (R/D/I); cross-verified ~35 counties (Cook + collar counties DuPage/Lake/Will/Kane/McHenry + Winnebago/Sangamon/Champaign/McLean/Rock Island/Peoria/Macon/Madison/St. Clair/Williamson/Coles/Jackson/Henry/Moultrie/Shelby/Lee/Piatt/Union and others) against county sheriff sites, county-gov pages and Ballotpedia \u2014 all matched. Party split: 80 Republican, 20 Democratic, 2 Independent (Calhoun\u2014William Heffington; Jersey\u2014Nick Manns; Independents left party-blank per Republican|Democratic enum). All sheriffs are partisan-elected to 4-year terms; most recent general Nov 2024, seated Dec 2024. Mid-term turnover captured: Sangamon Co.\u2014Paula Crouch appointed 2024-09-18 after Sheriff Jack Campbell resigned following the Sonya Massey shooting (first female Sangamon sheriff); ISBE Dec-2025 directory still lists Campbell but Crouch is the current incumbent. Cook County: Tom Dart (D), in office since 2006. Note: the 2016 constitutional-amendment vote abolished the elected Cook County Recorder, NOT the sheriff\u2014sheriffs remain elected in all 102 counties. Several long-term sheriffs (DuPage/Mendrick\u2014running for governor; McLean/Lane; Bureau/Reed; Christian/Kettelkamp; Kendall/Baird) are not seeking re-election in 2026 but remain incumbents as of 2026-07-04."
